8th Feb 2022 | Tues | 9.30pm
- heard a new term "Time to First Byte" (TTFB)
- The first chunk of content is usually 14kb of data
- heard of 'TCP Slow Start / 14 kb rule'
- ACK means acknowledgement
- there's something called send rate
- Parsing is the step the browser takes to turn the data it receives over the network into the DOM and CSSOM,
which is used by the rendered to paint a page to the screen.
